<div style="padding:2px 0 0 0;" class="description">From the album <i>A Rush of Blood to the Head</i>, Martin wrote "The Scientist" after listening to <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/George_Harrison" title="George Harrison">George Harrison</a>'s "<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/All_Things_Must_Pass_(song)" title="All Things Must Pass (song)">All Things Must Pass</a>".</div>
</div>
<hr />
<div class="haudio">
<div style="padding:2px 0;" class="fn"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Coldplay_-_Fix_You.ogg" title="File:Coldplay - Fix You.ogg">"Fix You"</a></div>
<div style="padding-right:4px;">
<div class="mediaContainer" style="position:relative;display:block;width:220px"><audio id="mwe_player_3" style="width:220px;height:23px" poster="//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.22wmf1/skins/common/images/icons/fileicon-ogg.png" controls="" preload="none" class="kskin" data-durationhint="30.000181405896" data-startoffset="0" data-mwtitle="Coldplay_-_Fix_You.ogg" data-mwprovider="local"><source src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/f/f1/Coldplay_-_Fix_You.ogg" type="audio/ogg; codecs=&quot;vorbis&quot;" data-title="Original Ogg file (41 kbps)" data-shorttitle="Ogg source" data-width="0" data-height="0" data-bandwidth="40601"></source>Sorry, your browser either has JavaScript disabled or does not have any supported player.<br />
